   =20
      Everything is securities fraud
   =20
 =20
I think sometimes about starting a spinoff Everything Is Securities Fraud n=
ewsletter that is just a weekly list of cases, with links but no other cont=
ent. There=E2=80=99s not much to say about them at this point, but they do =
keep happening. Two big ones from last week:=09=E2=80=9CBoeing=E2=80=99s Sa=
fety Claims Probed by SEC After Panel Blew Off Plane.=E2=80=9D=09=E2=80=9CI=
n Tesla Autopilot probe, US prosecutors focus on securities, wire fraud.=E2=
=80=9DIf someone is killed in a car crash, what is that? Why that=E2=80=99s=
 securities fraud. If a door flies off a plane in mid-air, what=E2=80=99s t=
hat? That, too, is securities fraud. Creating substantive regulations and d=
eterring misconduct in the real world is messy and complicated, but in the =
abstract world of finance, everything is securities fraud.
