<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">UBS</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The thing about investment bankers is =
that they spend all day talking to rich people about money =E2=80=94 meetin=
g with corporate chief executive officers and private equity investors to d=
iscuss mergers and financing =E2=80=94 but they would be hideously embarras=
sed to conclude those meetings by saying =E2=80=9Coh and what about you, do=
 you have enough life insurance, could we help you plan for retirement?=E2=
=80=9D The business of providing investment banking advice is totally separ=
ate from=C2=A0the business of providing personal financial advice. Even tho=
ugh the investment banker=E2=80=99s company also probably has a huge depart=
ment that provides personal financial advice and wealth management for rich=
 people. And makes a lot of reliable recurring revenue doing it. And is loo=
king to expand it.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And so every big investm=
ent bank will from time to time announce an initiative that is like =E2=80=
=9Cwe=E2=80=99re going to tell our investment bankers that they should real=
ly mention our wealth management business to their corporate-executive clie=
nts,=E2=80=9D and it really does tell the investment bankers that, and the =
investment bankers are like =E2=80=9Cyes we are team players and want to he=
lp our wealth management colleagues bring in more revenue,=E2=80=9D but the=
y shudder a little as they say it, and do they actually go out and pitch th=
e wealth management business? I don=E2=80=99t know, I=E2=80=99m not in the =
meetings.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One obvious problem with this app=
roach is that the wealth managers get paid for doing wealth management busi=
ness, and the investment bankers get paid for doing investment banking busi=
ness, and you can <em>tell </em>them to cross-sell because they are all tea=
m players, but <em>are </em>they? Whereas if you <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35362511.256340/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJn=
LmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDUtMTAvdWJzLXdlaWdocy1ib251cy1mb3ItaW52ZXN=
0bWVudC1iYW5rZXJzLXdoby1yZWZlci1yaWNoLWNsaWVudHM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDUxMzI0X01PTk=
VZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09M=
jQwNTEzJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe6b8b57a" =
